# Form Look & Feel Specification (Source of Truth)

Applies to:
- Inline filter/search forms above tables (e.g. Search + Created From/To)
- Modal “Edit/Create” forms (e.g. Edit Customer)
- Any standard CRUD form in the app

Goal:
- Modern SaaS admin feel: clean, airy, consistent spacing, clear hierarchy
- Subtle surfaces + borders, strong alignment, accessible focus/validation states
- Match the table styling: white card surfaces, light separators, rounded corners, calm UI

---

## Design Tokens (use as CSS variables or theme tokens)

- Page background: light neutral (e.g. #F6F8FB)
- Surface/card background: #FFFFFF
- Text: near-black (e.g. #111827)
- Muted text: grey (e.g. #6B7280)
- Border: light neutral (e.g. #E5E7EB)
- Primary: blue (e.g. #2563EB)
- Focus ring: primary at low opacity
- Error: red (soft background + clear text)
- Success: green (soft background + clear text)

---

## Global Form Rules

### Layout & Spacing
- Use a consistent vertical rhythm:
  - Field group spacing: 16px between fields (modal), 12–16px (inline filters)
  - Label-to-control spacing: 6–8px
  - Section padding inside cards/modals: 24px
- Align labels and inputs to a grid; avoid uneven widths.
- Prefer two-column layouts when space allows, but never cram fields.
- Use a max content width for long forms inside modals:
  - Inputs can be full-width; the modal controls the overall width.

### Labels
- Labels sit above inputs.
- Font size: 12–13px; font weight: 600
- Color: slightly muted (not black)
- Required indicator: red asterisk (*) next to label text.
- Helper text (optional): 12px muted, placed below the control.

### Inputs (text, email, phone, select, date)
- Height: 40px (standard), 44px (optional for touch)
- Border radius: 8px
- Border: 1px solid Border token
- Background: white
- Padding: 10–12px horizontal
- Placeholder text: muted and clearly distinguishable from typed text
- Focus state:
  - Border becomes Primary
  - Add a subtle focus ring/glow (low opacity)
- Disabled state:
  - Light neutral background
  - Muted text
  - Cursor indicates disabled
- Avoid harsh shadows on inputs; keep them flat with clean borders.

### Textarea
- Same border + radius as inputs
- Minimum height: 120px
- Vertical resize allowed (optional), horizontal resize disabled

### Validation States
- Invalid:
  - Border: error color
  - Show error text below field (12px), short and clear
- Valid (optional):
  - Border: success or keep neutral (prefer minimal “valid” chrome)
- Do not show validation errors until the user has interacted (touched) or attempted submit.

---

## Inline Filter/Search Form (Above Table)

### Container
- Must be inside a Card-style surface:
  - White background
  - 1px border
  - 12px radius
  - 16–20px padding
  - Subtle shadow optional (very light)
- The filter card should visually connect with the table card (same styling family).

### Layout
- Use a responsive grid:
  - Desktop: 3 columns (Search, Created From, Created To)
  - Tablet: 2 columns
  - Mobile: 1 column stacked
- Field widths should be consistent; date fields match input height and styling.

### Search Input
- Search placeholder: “Search by name, email, or phone…”
- Optional leading icon (magnifying glass) inside the input (subtle, muted).
- If a clear button exists, show only when there is text.

### Date Inputs
- Use the same input styling for date pickers.
- Calendar icon aligned right inside the control; muted by default.
- Ensure keyboard typing works (dd/mm/yyyy) if supported.

### Optional Actions (recommended)
- Add a compact “Clear filters” text button or secondary button on the right (optional).
- Any action buttons should be aligned right and not dominate the row.

---

## Modal Edit/Create Form (e.g. Edit Customer)

### Modal Container
- Modal:
  - White background
  - Radius: 12–16px
  - Subtle shadow/elevation
  - Width: 640–760px desktop; responsive down to mobile
- Overlay:
  - Dark translucent backdrop (subtle), clicking outside optionally closes.

### Modal Header
- Title left: “Edit Customer” / “New Customer”
  - Font size: 18–20px
  - Font weight: 700
- Close (X) icon button right:
  - Neutral, with subtle hover background
- Header padding: 20–24px
- Divider line under header: 1px light border

### Modal Body
- Padding: 24px
- Single column layout by default (full width fields)
- Group related fields with extra top margin and optional subheading (rare—keep simple).

### Modal Footer
- Divider line above footer: 1px light border
- Padding: 16–20px
- Buttons aligned right:
  - Secondary button: “Cancel”
  - Primary button: “Save”
- Button spacing: 12px gap
- Primary button should be visually dominant (solid Primary).
- Secondary button should be subtle (outline or soft surface).

---

## Buttons

### Primary Button
- Background: Primary
- Text: white
- Radius: 8–10px
- Height: 40px
- Padding: 0 16px
- Hover: slightly darker
- Disabled: reduced opacity + no hover

### Secondary Button
- Background: white (or very light neutral)
- Border: 1px solid Border
- Text: normal text color
- Hover: very light neutral background

### Icon Buttons (inside inputs/modals)
- No border
- Subtle hover background (light neutral)
- Tooltips for accessibility

---

## Typography
- Body text: 14–15px, normal weight
- Labels: 12–13px, semibold
- Helper/error: 12px
- Keep line length comfortable; avoid dense blocks.

---

## Accessibility & Interaction
- All controls must be keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus indicators required (do not remove outlines without replacement).
- Use aria-labels for icon-only buttons (close, clear, calendar).

---

## Do Not
- Do not use cramped spacing or mismatched input heights.
- Do not use heavy borders, harsh shadows, or overly saturated colors.
- Do not mix label placements (always above inputs).
- Do not use text links as primary form actions.

---

## Cursor Instruction (recommended)
Apply the form look and feel defined in this file to:
1) Inline filter/search forms above tables
2) Modal edit/create forms

Do not change business logic or API calls.
Only update layout, spacing, typography, colors/tokens, and component composition to match the spec exactly.
